            <article class="a-main  " data-article-url="https://www.wired.co.uk/article/future-of-apple" data-article-type="article" data-article-uid="yJzJeL8VAdm" data-meta-title="Has Apple finally bitten off way more than it can chew? | WIRED UK">
                    <header class="a-header has-hero">
                        <div class="a-header__wrapper">
                            <div class="a-header__content">
                                    <div class="a-header__tag">


                                        <a href="https://www.wired.co.uk/topic/apple"  class="a-header__tag__primary">Apple</a>

                                    </div>

                                    <h1 class="a-header__title">Has Apple finally bitten off way more than it can chew?</h1>

                                    <div class="a-header__teaser has-bbcode"><p class="bb-p">Apple used to be about changing the world one magic box at a time. Now it’s fighting to conquer TV drama, healthcare, money, news and much else besides</p></div>

                                <hr class="a-header__separator" />

                                <div class="a-header__about">

                                        <div class="a-header__byline">

                                        <span class="a-header__byline-item">
                                            <span class="a-header__byline-prefix">By</span>
                                            <span class="a-header__byline-name"><a href="/profile/john-arlidge">John Arlidge</a></span>
                                        </span>


                                        </div>

                                            <div class="a-header__date">09 Apr 2020</div>
                                </div>


